Title: An exact universal amplitude ratio for percolation
Authors: Katherine A. Seaton
Comments: 5 pages, LaTeX, submitted to J. Phys. A. One paragraph rewritten to
  correct errors
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Statistical Mechanics
Journal-ref: J.Phys. A34 (2001) L759-L762
\\
  The universal amplitude ratio $\tilde{R}_{\xi}$ for percolation in two
dimensions is determined exactly using results for the dilute A model in regime
1, by way of a relationship with the q-state Potts model for q<4.
